    <text id="R13770151T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Confederate Cavalry General John C. Vaughn reports to General Braxton Bragg on
                    the June 6, 1864, aftermath of the Battle of Piedmont. Vaughn reports the Union
                    occupation of Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Gen. B. BRAGG. </name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-06-06">June 6, 1864.</date>
                        <name type="place">WAYNESBOROUGH,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>Went in the fight yesterday with an aggregate of 5,600. I have not over 3,000
                    effective men, including Imboden's cavalry, 800. I don't know where Gen. Elzey
                    is; think he has gone toward Charlottesville. Enemy occupied Staunton this
                    morning Crook will from junction to-night or to-morrow with Hunter. Crook's
                    force reported at 10,000. McCausland and Jackson are falling back upon this
                    place. Hunter has, I think, 10,000 men, with twenty-four pieces of artillery;
                    Crook has thirty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>J. C. VAUGHN,<lb/> Brig.-Gen., Cmdg.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
